# Orkestra environment template
#
# Copy this file to docker/.env via `make init` (recommended — auto-fills
# the *_REPLACE_* placeholders below with random secrets, generates
# JWT keys, and prints next steps) or manually:
#
#     cp docker/.env.example docker/.env
#     scripts/init.sh       # or `make init` from the repo root
#
# Module-level configuration (OAuth credentials, OpenAPI billing / company
# tokens, Stripe keys, SMTP, AI provider keys, Hindsight URL, Memgraph URI,
# Gotenberg URL, per-module enable flags) is owned by ConfigService and
# managed at /admin/modules after first login. The variables in this file
# are limited to:
#   1. Process-scoped infrastructure read at boot before ConfigService
#      exists (Mongo URI, Redis URL, JWT keys, cookies, etc.)
#   2. Encryption keys that bootstrap ConfigService itself
#   3. Sales / RAG runtime knobs not yet migrated to ConfigSchema
# See docker/CLAUDE.md for the full bucket split.

# ============================================
# ENVIRONMENT IDENTIFICATION
# ============================================
APP_NAME=orkestra
# development | staging | production. Drives compose-file selection in
# orkestra.sh and the cookie/CORS/rate-limit defaults inside the backend.
ENV=development

# Dev-only knob: which docker-compose dev file does orkestra.sh use?
#   public     — docker-compose.dev-public.yml (default; public Alpine
#                images, no registry auth required, fork-friendly).
#   chainguard — docker-compose.dev.yml         (Chainguard hardened
#                base images, requires a dhi.io subscription).
# Unset = public. Switch to "chainguard" only if your operator has
# the dhi.io contract.
# DEV_COMPOSE_VARIANT=public

# ============================================
# SERVER CONFIGURATION
# ============================================
BACKEND_PORT=3000
BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

FRONTEND_PORT=8080
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:8080

# Per-tier frontend origins for verification + reset email links.
# Empty falls back to FRONTEND_URL. Set CLIENT_FRONTEND_URL to the Tier-2
# client SPA host so signups landing through CLIENT_API_HOST get verify
# links pointing back at the client SPA, not the operator console.
OPERATOR_FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:8080
CLIENT_FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:8081

# CORS — legacy single-host fallback. Per-audience overrides below.
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:8080,http://localhost:8081

# ADR-0003 host split — operator + client audiences served from one
# binary, dispatched by Host header. In dev an unmatched Host falls
# through to the operator mux so plain `curl http://localhost:3000`
# keeps working. In staging/prod an unmatched Host returns 421.
CONSOLE_HOST=console.localhost
CLIENT_API_HOST=api.localhost

# Per-audience CORS / rate-limit overrides; empty falls back to the
# legacy CORS_ORIGINS / RATE_LIMIT_* values above.
OPERATOR_CORS_ORIGINS=
CLIENT_CORS_ORIGINS=
OPERATOR_RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS_PER_MINUTE=
OPERATOR_RATE_LIMIT_BURST=
CLIENT_RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS_PER_MINUTE=
CLIENT_RATE_LIMIT_BURST=

# Frontend Vite Environment Variables
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
VITE_WS_URL=ws://localhost:3000/ws
VITE_PUBLIC_URL='/'
VITE_ENV=development

# ============================================
# SECURITY — COOKIES & SESSION
# ============================================
# 32-byte hex random; generated by `make init`.
COOKIE_SECRET=REPLACE_WITH_RANDOM_HEX_64_COOKIE_SECRET
COOKIE_NAME_REFRESH=orkestra_cookie_refresh
COOKIE_NAME_ACCESS=orkestra_cookie_access
COOKIE_DOMAIN=localhost
# ADR-0003 PR-D D-9: per-audience refresh-cookie scopes.
# Operator surface (console.*) and client surface (api.*) cookies must
# not share a parent domain in production-like environments — set both
# explicitly so a session minted on one host cannot be replayed on the
# other. Empty falls back to COOKIE_DOMAIN above (single-host behaviour).
OPERATOR_COOKIE_DOMAIN=console.localhost
CLIENT_COOKIE_DOMAIN=api.localhost
COOKIE_HTTP_ONLY=true
COOKIE_SECURE=false
COOKIE_SAME_SITE=lax
COOKIE_MAX_AGE=86400000
ALLOW_LOCALHOST_REDIRECTS=true

# ============================================
# JWT AUTHENTICATION (RS256)
# ============================================
# Keys are generated by scripts/generate-jwt-keys.sh (invoked by `make init`).
# Do NOT commit docker/keys/ to git.
JWT_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=/app/keys/jwt-private.pem
JWT_PUBLIC_KEY_PATH=/app/keys/jwt-public.pem
JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY=1h
JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY=30d

# ============================================
# ENCRYPTION KEYS (bootstrap ConfigService + per-tenant KMS)
# ============================================
# AES-256-GCM key (64 hex chars) used to encrypt every secret stored in
# module_configs (OAuth secrets, Stripe keys, OpenAPI tokens, SMTP password).
# Rotating this invalidates every stored secret in the admin UI.
OAUTH_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_RANDOM_HEX_64_OAUTH_ENCRYPTION

# Compliance KMS master key — wraps per-tenant DEKs (32 bytes hex).
# Losing this invalidates every wrapped DEK; rotate carefully.
ORKESTRA_KMS_MASTER_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_RANDOM_HEX_64_KMS_MASTER

# ============================================
# DATABASE — MONGODB
# ============================================
MONGO_HOST=mongodb
MONGO_PORT=27017
MONGO_ROOT_USERNAME=admin
MONGO_ROOT_PASSWORD=REPLACE_WITH_RANDOM_HEX_32_MONGO_PASSWORD
MONGO_DATABASE=orkestra

# ============================================
# CACHE — REDIS
# ============================================
REDIS_HOST=redis
REDIS_PORT=6379
REDIS_PASSWORD=REPLACE_WITH_RANDOM_HEX_32_REDIS_PASSWORD
REDIS_DB=0

# ============================================
# CONTAINER CONTROL (backend manages module infra: hindsight, memgraph)
# ============================================
# Host docker group GID — backend joins it to read /var/run/docker.sock.
# Run `getent group docker | cut -d: -f3` to confirm on a new host (Linux).
# On macOS / Docker Desktop the value is typically irrelevant — the socket
# is owned by the user, leave the default and ignore the warning.
DOCKER_GID=987
CONTAINER_CONTROL_ENABLED=true

# ============================================
# OBSERVABILITY
# ============================================
LOG_LEVEL=info
# Leave empty when the observability stack (docker-compose.observability.yml)
# isn't running — tracer falls back to no-op and avoids exporter retries.
# When you bring up the stack, set:
#   OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://orkestra-otel:4318
# Scheme must be present — the otlptrace/otlplog SDKs default to HTTPS when
# given bare host:port; the collector listens on plain HTTP inside docker.
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_INSECURE=true
OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=orkestra-backend
OTEL_TRACES_ENABLED=false
OTEL_METRICS_ENABLED=false
OTEL_LOGS_ENABLED=false

# ADR-0005 Phase A — structured request logger knobs (defaults are fine).
# LOG_HTTP_SKIP_PATHS: comma list of exact paths to suppress request-log
#   lines for. Defaults: /health,/ready,/metrics,/openapi.json. When set,
#   REPLACES the default list — include the defaults explicitly to extend.
# LOG_HTTP_SLOW_THRESHOLD_MS: requests slower than this get
#   slog.Bool("slow", true) stamped on the line so you can query
#   {slow=true} in Loki without bucketing.
LOG_HTTP_SKIP_PATHS=
LOG_HTTP_SLOW_THRESHOLD_MS=1000

# ADR-0005 Phase C — per-module log level overrides. Each LOG_LEVEL_<MODULE>
# overrides the global LOG_LEVEL for that module only. Module names are
# lowercase (LOG_LEVEL_RAG matches the rag addon, LOG_LEVEL_BILLING matches
# billing, etc.). Unparseable values are silently ignored — a typo never
# breaks boot.
# LOG_LEVEL_RAG=debug
# LOG_LEVEL_BILLING=warn

# ============================================
# RATE LIMITING (dev defaults; staging/prod compose overrides)
# ============================================
RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS_PER_MINUTE=1000
RATE_LIMIT_BURST=100

# ============================================
# DEVELOPMENT SPECIFIC
# ============================================
DEBUG=true
PRETTY_LOGS=true

# ============================================
# SALES INTELLIGENCE (still runtime-read by cfg.Sales.*)
# ============================================
SALES_MAX_CONCURRENCY=5
SALES_DEFAULT_LOCALE=en
SALES_QUICK_TIMEOUT=60s
SALES_FULL_TIMEOUT=5m
SALES_SCRAPER_TIMEOUT=30s
SALES_SCRAPER_MAX_DEPTH=3

# ============================================
# RAG (still runtime-read by cfg.RAG.{ChunkSize,ChunkOverlap,DefaultTopK})
# ============================================
RAG_CHUNK_SIZE=512
RAG_CHUNK_OVERLAP=50
RAG_DEFAULT_TOP_K=10

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL FIRST-BOOT SEEDS
# ============================================
# Every variable below is OPTIONAL and READ ONLY ONCE — by
# ConfigService.SeedFromModules when its `module_configs` document does
# not yet exist. After first boot they are no-ops; edits flow through
# /admin/modules instead.
#
# Login with email/password works out-of-the-box without any of these.
# Add OAuth providers, SMTP, Stripe, AI keys, etc. via the admin UI after
# first login, OR pre-seed them here by uncommenting and filling in.
#
# OAuth — Google
# OAUTH_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# OAUTH_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
# OAUTH_GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URL=http://localhost:3000/v1/auth/oauth/google/callback
# OAUTH_GOOGLE_ANDROID_CLIENT_ID=
# OAUTH_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID=
#
# OAuth — Apple
# OAUTH_APPLE_TEAM_ID=
# OAUTH_APPLE_CLIENT_ID=
# OAUTH_APPLE_KEY_ID=
# OAUTH_APPLE_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=/app/keys/apple.p8
# OAUTH_APPLE_REDIRECT_URL=http://localhost:3000/v1/auth/oauth/apple/callback
#
# OAuth — Discord / GitHub
# OAUTH_DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=
# OAUTH_DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=
# OAUTH_DISCORD_REDIRECT_URL=
# OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
# OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
# OAUTH_GITHUB_REDIRECT_URL=
#
# Notification (SMTP). Default `noop` provider just logs to stdout —
# verification / reset emails won't be delivered but the backend works.
# NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_PROVIDER=smtp
# NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_FROM=noreply@example.com
# SMTP_HOST=
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USERNAME=
# SMTP_PASSWORD=
#
# Billing / FatturaPA (Italian electronic invoicing — IT-only addon).
# OPENAPI_BILLING_BEARER_TOKEN=
# OPENAPI_BILLING_BASE_URL=https://sdi.openapi.it
# OPENAPI_BILLING_FISCAL_ID=
# OPENAPI_BILLING_RECIPIENT_CODE=
# OPENAPI_SANDBOX_MODE=true
# BILLING_WEBHOOK_URL=http://localhost:3000/v1/billing/webhooks/sdi
# BILLING_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
#
# Company lookup (Italian business registry — IT-only addon).
# OPENAPI_COMPANY_BEARER_TOKEN=
#
# AI Models
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
#
# Memgraph / Hindsight (managed by the graph + agents modules — auto-started)
# GRAPH_URI=bolt://orkestra-memgraph:7687
# HINDSIGHT_URL=http://orkestra-hindsight:8888
# HINDSIGHT_NAMESPACE=orkestra
#
# Documents (Gotenberg — PDF rendering)
# GOTENBERG_URL=http://gotenberg:3000
#
# Stripe (payments)
# STRIPE_API_KEY=
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
